        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "## DTPA Binding Constants (log K for M + L ⇌ ML)\n\n**DTPA** (diethylenetriaminepentaacetic acid, ligand_6356) is a powerful octadentate chelator with 5 carboxylate and 3 amine donor groups. Since you didn't specify a metal, here are the **1:1 formation constants** (log K) for all 20 metals available in the database. The table shows representative values at **25 °C, I = 0.1 M** in water, sorted by binding strength:\n\n| Metal | log K (25 °C, I ≈ 0.1 M) | log K (I = 0) | Electrolyte |\n|-------|--------------------------|---------------|-------------|\n| Fe³⁺ | 28.0 | 27.3 | KNO₃ |\n| Bi³⁺ | 26.73 | 27.1 | KNO₃ |\n| Th⁴⁺ | 26.2 | 26.64 | KNO₃ |\n| Ga³⁺ | 24.0 | 25.0 | KNO₃ |\n| Sm³⁺ | 22.1 | 22.34 | KNO₃ |\n| Yb³⁺ | 22.1 | 22.62 | KNO₃ |\n| Eu³⁺ | 22.1 | 22.39 | KNO₃ |\n| Nd³⁺ | 21.4 | 21.6 | KNO₃ |\n| Cu²⁺ | 21.2 | 21.53 | KNO₃ |\n| Ni²⁺ | 20.17 | 20.32 | KNO₃ |\n| Cd²⁺ | 19.0 | 19.31 | KNO₃ |\n| Co²⁺ | 18.6 | 19.26 | KNO₃ |\n| Pb²⁺ | 18.69 | 18.96 | KNO₃ |\n| Zn²⁺ | 18.29 | 18.75 | KNO₃ |\n| Al³⁺ | 18.1 | 18.4 | KNO₃ |\n| Fe²⁺ | 16.0 | 16.55 | KNO₃ |\n| Mn²⁺ | 15.1 | 15.6 | KNO₃ |\n| Ca²⁺ | 10.58 | 10.74 | KNO₃ |\n| Mg²⁺ | 9.02 | 9.3 | KNO₃ |",
